sections.content:
“acceptable internationally recognised accounting standards” means 
accounting  standards  issued  by  other  accounting  standards  issuing 
bodies  granted  recognition  by  the  Board  under  section  26A;

“Audit  Oversight  Board”  means  the  Audit  Oversight  Board 
established under section 31C of the Securities Commission Act 1993 
[Act 498];

(a) to provide its views to the Board on any matter which the 
Board  seeks  to  undertake  or  implement  in  relation  to  the 
Board’s functions under section 7;

the President of the Malaysian Institute of Accountants or 
his representative who shall be a council member of the 
Malaysian Institute of Accountants;

to issue, approve, review, revise, amend, substitute, suspend, 
defer, withdraw or revoke any issues bulletin in whole or in 
part;

to  conduct  such  public  consultation  as  may  be  necessary  in 
order  to  determine  the  contents  of  accounting  concepts, 
principles and standards;

(a)  the  Securities  Commission  in  respect  of  a  corporation  listed 
on  the  stock  exchange  or  any  entity  supervised  by  the 
Securities Commission under the securities laws;
